sentence: The Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJI) jumped as high as 86.5 points in intraday trading, and despite paring most of its lead, ended at a multi-year best.
"After a good start to the session, we lost steam as the day wore on," said Schaeffer's Senior Technical Strategist Ryan Detrick.
"The jobs data was considered promising.
It wasn't too strong and it wasn't too weak.
All in all, though, it was a slow Friday after the initial jobs fireworks."

Keep reading to see what else was on our radar today:
• Does the "hated rally" in equities have the legs to run higher ?
• Plus, options traders ramped up their positions on Wall Street freshmen Groupon Inc ( GRPN ) , Facebook Inc ( FB ) , and Pandora Media Inc ( P ) .
And now, a look at the numbers...
The S&P 500 Index (SPX - 1,460.93) and Nasdaq Composite (COMP - 3,136.19) were higher in early trading, but dipped below the breakeven mark as the closing bell approached.
The SPX slipped to a fractional loss on the day, but saw a 1.4% rise for the week.
Meanwhile, the COMP posted a deficit of 13.3 points, or 0.4%, but enjoyed a weekly return of 0.6%.
The CBOE Market Volatility Index (VIX - 14.33) stayed below its 20-day moving average, and notched its lowest close since Sept. 24.
The VIX inched 0.2 point, or 1.5%, lower for the day, and backpedaled 8.9% for the week.
Today's highlight : "With the unemployment numbers out of the way, we can focus on earnings season, which starts next week," said Detrick.
"Alcoa Inc. (AA) kicks things off on Tuesday."
• See more proof that this current market rally isn't over .
• Schaeffer's Equities Analyst Tony Venosa revisited the technical and sentiment makeup of Cisco Systems, Inc. (CSCO) .
• Celgene Corporation (CELG), Wal-Mart Stores, Inc. (WMT) and Zynga Inc (ZNGA) made record-breaking runs today .

• Option Volume Briefs: beleaguered Groupon Inc ( GRPN ) saw a rise in short-term call buying, while put writers bet on near-term support for the Consumer Discretionary Select Sector SPDR Fund (NYSEARCA:XLY) .
• An unwinding of pessimism could fuel bigger gains for Exxon Mobil Corporation ( XOM ) .
• Put buyers placed their bets on Applied Materials, Inc. (AMAT) and First Solar, Inc. (FSLR) .
• Option bears believe more downside is ahead for Facebook Inc ( FB ) and Pandora Media Inc ( P ) .
• The brokerage crowd weighed in on human resources specialist Automatic Data Processing (ADP) and biotech firm Biogen Idec Inc. (BIIB) .
For today's activity in commodities, options, and more, head to page 2.
Though the conflict between Syria and Turkey was a boon for oil futures on Thursday , the commodity slipped today on growing concerns for global demand.
By the close, November-dated crude lost $1.83, or 2%, to settle at $89.88 a barrel.
For the week, black gold retreated 2.5%.
Gold futures also headed south today, as a better-than-expected unemployment report dimmed stimulus hopes.
Against this backdrop, gold for December delivery retreated $15.70, or 0.9%, closing at $1,780.80 an ounce.
The malleable metal inched higher by 0.4% during the week.
